> This plant-based version of a classic Italian comfort meal is sure to satisfy! You'll pan-fry tofu to golden-brown perfection, then coat in a velvety, savory mushroom sauce. It's served atop creamy mashed potatoes with a side of tender, garlicky roasted green beans for a delicious, hearty dinner. Who says restaurant-style dining at home can't be vegan?

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

> For a smoother texture, peel potatoes first.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain. Return potatoes to pot; keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

== Roasted Green Beans ==

While potatoes cook, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Open and drain @tofu{1%unit}; press out excess water with #paper towels{}. Halve crosswise, then stand tofu upright and halve vertically. Lay flat and cut into ½-inch cubes.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @oil{1%teaspoon}, one clove of garlic, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until tender and browned, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Tofu ==

Meanwhile, in a #shallow dish{}, combine half the @flour{2%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Add tofu; toss until evenly coated.

Heat a large drizzle of @oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add coated tofu and cook, turning occasionally, until golden on all sides, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

Add @vegan mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} to pot with potatoes. Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed.

> If potatoes have cooled, mash over medium-low heat.

Season with salt and pepper.

== Mushroom Marsala ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for tofu over medium heat. Add mushrooms, remaining flour, salt, and pepper. Stir to coat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are softened and lightly crusted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1%unit}, remaining garlic, and 2/3 cup water. Bring to a simmer; cook until slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Add tofu to marsala sauce and stir gently until evenly coated.

== To Serve ==

Divide mashed potatoes and green beans between #shallow bowls{}. Top mashed potatoes with tofu and marsala sauce. Garnish with parsley and serve.